                <h3>Whirlpool</h3>
                <p>
                  Whirlpool is a well-known and reputable brand in the home appliance industry, known for its durability and reliability. However, even the best appliances can experience issues over time. Common repairs for Whirlpool bar refrigerators include thermostat replacements, compressor repairs, and door gasket replacements. Due to the availability of Whirlpool parts and the brand's widespread usage, repair costs are generally moderate. A thermostat replacement might cost around <b>$150</b>, while more extensive repairs like compressor replacements can go up to <b>$400</b>. Whirlpool's extensive service network also makes it easier and often cheaper to find qualified technicians, which can help keep repair costs reasonable.
