                <h3>GE (General Electric)</h3>
                <p>
                  GE appliances are also a staple in many households, known for their advanced features and robust performance. Repairing a GE bar refrigerator can be slightly more expensive due to the specialized parts and technology involved. Common issues might include problems with the evaporator fan motor, condenser coils, or control boards. The cost for a simple repair, like replacing a fan motor, might be around <b>$200</b>, but more complex issues like a faulty control board or compressor can push the repair costs up to <b>$500</b>. GE also has a strong network of authorized repair technicians, which can be beneficial for ensuring the longevity and performance of your appliance.
                </p>

                <h3>Samsung</h3>
